dc_title_s: Iberian Peninsula 1:250,000: Montalban, sheet 44. Series A.M.S. M581
dc_description_s: United States. Army Map Service. North Decimal Degree 41.0000. South Decimal Degree 40.0000. East Decimal Degree -0.0000. West Decimal Degree -1.0000. Alternate title: Montalban, Spain. Polyconic projection. With Spanish-English glossary. Relief shown by 100 m. contour interval, gradient tint and spot heights. Standard map series designation: A.M.S. M581. "Compiled from Spain, 1:50,000, Instituto Geografico, 1923-38; Spain 1:200,000, Cuartel General del Generalisimo, sheets 37, undated and 47, 1929; Spain, 1:200,000, Instituto Geografico, PROVINCIA DE TERUEL, 1935 and PROVINCIA DE CASTELLON DE LA PLANA, undated; Iberian Peninsula, 1:250,000, GSGS, 1941; Spain and Portugal Road Map, 1:400,000, AMS, sheets 45 and 47, Third Edition, 1943; Railways in Spain and Portugal 1:1,500,000, GSGS, 1941, corrected from Intelligence Reports, 1942-44. Partially revised from aerial photography, 1943.".
